because that's kind of

00:31:33.890 --> 00:31:35.850
irrelevant in this whole thing.

00:31:35.850 --> 00:31:39.450
But also that the cost of
them simply printing on demand

00:31:39.450 --> 00:31:40.240
is so cheap.

00:31:40.240 --> 00:31:44.230
In particular, the dynamic that
pushes the price up, especially

00:31:44.230 --> 00:31:45.920
for Lulu.com-- this
is one of things--

00:31:45.920 --> 00:31:48.000
is if they wanted to
put it into a channel

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:50.110
so that people would
actually buy it somewhere,

00:31:50.110 --> 00:31:53.050
which I thought was kind of
a requirement for a book.

00:31:53.050 --> 00:31:55.930
They basically need to
build in high enough price

00:31:55.930 --> 00:31:59.840
because the retail place is
going to take half of that.

00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:02.340
So it has to be high enough
that the place that's selling it

00:32:02.340 --> 00:32:05.050
is taking half of it, and then
all of their cost and profit

00:32:05.050 --> 00:32:06.390
are built into the rest.

00:32:06.390 --> 00:32:08.930
With CreateSpace
you have the option

00:32:08.930 --> 00:32:11.710
